race.comment: A good contest. HEROIC MISS (11) stepped up and was narrowly beaten here this grade over 1200m. She's ready to win and will carry just 52kg with the claim. Has more to give and flies third-up. Tough to beat. HASTEN DELIGHT (12) spiked his figure, winning a CL5 easily at Ipswich from the pace. Tumbles in weight, and that brings him right into it. EDITED BY (2) led and won a 78 at Rosehill before the spell but was outgraded at Stakes level at Doomben first-up. Has been kept up to the mark with a trial and his second-up record is sharp. Has the blinkers on for the first time and quick improvement is on the cards. LIVING FREE (8) goes well fresh and has bene trialling nicely.
